FBIS4-45460 "jptdd027__l94038" JPRS-TDD-94-027L JPRS Narcotics 12 June 1994 EAST ASIA VIETNAM Thai Binh Authorities Step Up Campaign Against Opium Den Thai Binh Authorities Step Up Campaign Against Opium Den Owners, Drug Traffickers BK1306110994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 0500 GMT 12 Jun 94 BK1306110994 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network Vietnamese BFN [Text] The Thai Binh Province people's committee has met with the sectors concerned and districts, towns, wards, and villages with opium addicts to discuss measures to implement a rehabilitation program. There are more than 680 opium addicts in 119 villages, wards, and towns in Thai Binh Province. More than 300 of those addicts are seriously affected by the habit. With assistance from the central government, the province has obtained a relatively sufficient amount of medicines to carry out a rehabilitation program. It was reported that following a 40 day-long campaign against social vices, Thai Binh Province discovered and took action against more than 200 opium den owners and drug traffickers. Legal proceedings were also initiated against 50 brothel owners and 160 criminals.
